        "title": "fix(llm): prevent reasoning_content leak when reasoning is disabled",
        "body": "Issue: Some models (e.g., MiMo V2.5 Pro) return reasoning_content in streaming deltas even when reasoning is explicitly disabled. The generic openai-completions provider extracts these fields unconditionally, causing internal thinking to leak into the final output.\r\n​Fix: Added a reasoningEnabled check before iterating through reasoningFields. If reasoning is off, the fields are safely ignored and stripped from the normal content flow.",
